On behalf of the great people of New Mexico, I will end Kamala's war on American energy. They, you're not going to have any energy. You know, they talk about PA, no fracking. And we will blast our way through into a city and environmentally friendly way. You know what happens? The battery is so big and so heavy that you will have to carry it in like a wagon in the back. Okay? They'll be pulling a battery along in a wagon and the battery's so heavy. They don't even know if the tank is going to have the power to do it. The whole thing is crazy. It doesn't go far. It doesn't have the right torque. These are minor details. The whole tank is so heavy that if it goes over a bridge, you're going to have to rebuild all the bridges. Same thing with the trucks. They want to make all trucks, all trucks, all electric. The problem is they weigh 2 1/2 times more because of the battery. They don't go far enough. And because of the weight, by the way, it would mean we would have to build and rebuild every bridge in the United States of America has to be rebuilt to handle the weight of all electric trucks. I said to the head of the truck, or one guy's 28,000 trucks. I said, that's a lot. He's been buying him his whole life. He said, I've been buying trucks for 50 years, sir. And every year they got better, bigger, stronger, more beautiful. We build those apartments on the back of that trailer right now. So you'd be proud to live in one of them. I said, I don't know about that. I'm not sure. Maybe I would. I probably would. They're beautiful, you see. But every year, he said, for 50 years, they've got more efficient. They've gotten better. And now they want us to go all electric. And we'd be going back 50 years and much more 50 years ago, truck was better than the best electric truck today. So I said, did you explain that to the authorities as they burst into your office to demand that you go all electric? I explained it. What they say, we don't give a damn. We want you to go all electric. This is what we're dealing with. It's like gestapo stuff. They use that term. It's like gestapo stuff. What they're doing to our country is unbelievable. And you talk about a supply chain. I said, how many stops would you have to make for electric six? The LA, NY to LA 6 stops are. And we have no chargers. I said, that's a problem too. Do you know they built eight charging stations? You know what a charging station? It's the same thing as the pump with gasoline, except electric is there. It comes to you. You put it in, right? Do you hear the story? $9 billion they've spent for eight charging stations in the mid-west. So you're about ready to run out of electric and they say, sir, if you go 300 miles to the north, there's a charging station up there. It would cost us to do the necessary charging stations. It would cost us, they say, about $10T. That's like $10T to do the necessary. And you know what? I'm not against electric. I think they're incredible. I think they have a purpose. I think Tesla's great. I think Elon, he endorsed me, gave me the best. I think they have a great purpose. But you can't go all electric. You want gasoline powered cars. You want hybrids.
